"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896408","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-09","<p>My Department maintains close contact with Gypsy, Roma and Traveller stakeholder groups, and officials meet community representatives quarterly to discuss policy questions and give Gypsy, Roma and Traveller communities a voice at the heart of Government.</p><p>Unauthorised developments and encampments, and the recently-launched consultation, have been discussed at these meetings, with my noble Friend, Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth, the Minister responsible for Gypsy and Traveller equality, in attendance. Officials have also attended other relevant events concerning the consultation, such as the one organised by the All-Party Parliamentary Group for Gypsies, Travellers and Roma in the winter of 2017.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-05-09T15:08:59.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896408/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896408/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Government's consultation, Powers for dealing with unauthorised development and encampments, launched on 5 April 2018, what meetings he has had with representatives of the Gypsy, Traveller and Roma communities (a) prior to and (b) since launching that consultation.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","140713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896409","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-09","<p>My officials are organising, in collaboration with members of the Gypsy, Roma and Traveller communities, several workshops throughout May and June, which will offer members of these communities a chance to discuss the consultation and formulate responses.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-05-09T15:08:13.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896409/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896409/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Government's consultation, Powers for dealing with unauthorised development and encampments, launched on 5 April 2018, what meetings he plans to have with representatives of the Gypsy, Traveller and Roma communities before that consultation closes on 15 June 2018.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","140714"
