"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896469","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Civil Service’s policy since February 2015 has been not to use confidentiality agreements in settlement agreements on termination of employment. The Department’s approach is to not use non-disclosure agreements for settlement agreements and instead be open and transparent with agreement outcomes.</p><p> </p><p>Based on the information available for the Department of Transport, including executive agencies, the number of non-disclosure agreements used are:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>2018</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total number of non-disclosure agreements his Department has signed with employees</p></td><td><p>Data not held</p></td><td><p>Data not held</p></td><td><p>Less than 5</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-05-14T14:50:03.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896469/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896469/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896469/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Department for Transport: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many non-disclosure agreements his Department has signed with employees in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","140816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896470","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-09","<p>We do not hold a central record of ‘settlement agreements’. The use of non disclosure settlement agreements would be extremely rare and would always comply with the Cabinet Office’s central guidance. We believe that no non-disclosure agreements have been used in the period<em>.</em></p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-05-09T14:41:10.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896470/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896470/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896470/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-02","Department for Work and Pensions: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many non-disclosure agreements her Department has signed with employees in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","140817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896471","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-15","<p>The Government does not currently provide funding for safety rails around slurry tanks in England. However, we keep the focus of our Rural Development Programme schemes under review. If we were to introduce a scheme for slurry management under the programme in future we would consider what it should fund.</p><p>All UK administrations have their own EU funded Rural Development Programmes. Any funding for slurry tank safety rails in Northern Ireland through this means would be a matter for the Northern Ireland programme.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-15T15:14:41.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896471/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896471/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896471/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-02","Agriculture: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of introducing a grant to encourage farmers with slurry tanks to erect more effective safety railings around those tanks.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","140861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896472","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport is not able to provide a response to cover the last five years. In 2017, there were five non-disclosure agreements, all relating to recruitment of temporary staff. Non-disclosure agreements are put in place in exceptional circumstances. Non-disclosure agreements in DCMS are only used for temporary staff who will work on sensitive information, where commercially or politically sensitive.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-05-14T17:04:11.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896472/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896472/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896472/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-05-02","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many non-disclosure agreements his Department has signed with employees in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","140818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896473","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-10","<p>The number of non-disclosure agreements signed by DFID in each of the last five years is shown in the below table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fewer than 5</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-05-10T14:55:54.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896473/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896473/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896473/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-02","Department for International Development: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many non-disclosure agreements her Department has signed with employees in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","140819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896474","Scotland Office","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Scotland Office has not signed any non-disclosure agreements with any employees in any of the last five years.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-05-14T10:41:36.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896474/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896474/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896474/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-05-02","Scotland Office: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many non-disclosure agreements his Department has signed with employees in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","140820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896475","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-05-10","<p>As the number of non-disclosure agreements in the last five years is fewer than five, in order to comply with Data Protection Act requirements I am unable to provide this number as a full answer would risk the identification of individuals.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2018-05-10T09:43:14.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896475/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896475/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-05-02","Northern Ireland Office: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many non-disclosure agreements her Department has signed with employees in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","140821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896476","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-08","<p>Farmers in Great Britain are required to report accidents that cause defined injuries to people under the Reporting of Injuries, Diseases and Dangerous Occurrences Regulations 2013. Reports made in compliance with these regulations do not contain sufficient detail to enable identification of all incidents that are specifically related to slurry storage.</p><p> </p><p>In the case of incidents that have caused death, the Health and Safety Executive publishes annual reports of fatal injuries in agriculture in Great Britain. In the last three years for which figures have been published, the following deaths related to slurry storage were recorded:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of deaths</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-05-08T10:32:37.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896476/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896476/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-02","Agriculture: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many farm accidents were reported involving a slurry tank or other slurry storage in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","140862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896477","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-09","<p>The management of parks and any exercise equipment within those spaces is the responsibility of each local authority. The Government does not hold data on the use or value for money of park exercise equipment.</p><p>The Parks Action Group, which was created following the Select Committee response to the Inquiry on the future of public parks, is reviewing a range of issues relating to parks and green spaces in England, including developing priority work streams on usage and value of parks. The Group has committed to review the need for structured physical facilities within parks and will report back to Parliament in the Autumn.</p><p>Many local authorities already work very closely on health and wellbeing issues and are keen to develop opportunities for play. Best practice models are shared in the Local Government Association, which is a member of the Parks Action Group and will be a pivotal partner in sharing the learning and best practice from the Group with local authorities.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-05-09T15:11:17.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896477/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896477/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Exercise: Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will make an assessment of the level of (a) use and (b) value for money of park exercise equipment.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","140863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896478","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>There are no plans to introduce further prohibitions of smoking on publicly-owned property not covered by the Health Act 2006. Smokefree policies have been successfully introduced across the Government estate through administrative means, without relying on a statutory ban.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-14T15:36:08.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896478/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896478/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Smoking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department plans to prohibit smoking on publicly owned property not covered by the Health Act 2006.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","140864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896479","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-11","<p>We are concerned about the recent church closures in Algeria. Our Ambassador in Algeria has been in touch with the Protestant Church of Algeria, who have raised the closures with the Algerian Ministry of Interior. Our Ambassador will also raise with the Algerian authorities. The Algerian Constitution provides for freedom of conscience and religion. Foreign and Commonwealth Office Minister Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon discussed the importance of freedom of religion and belief with the Algerian Minister for Religious Affairs in October 2017.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-11T13:39:11.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896479/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896479/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Algeria: Christianity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the Algerian Government on the forced closure of Christian churches in that country.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","140865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896480","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-08","<p>The total amount allocated to UK aquaculture through the European Fisheries Fund (EFF) for the period 2007 to 2013 was £6,332,265. EFF funding was co-financed with £4,026,108 of national funding (UK Exchequer) along with private investment of £17,644,734, resulting in total investment in the aquaculture sector of £28,003,107.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-08T16:36:02.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896480/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896480/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-02","Aquaculture: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate he has made of the total amount allocated to UK aquaculture through the European Fisheries Fund for the period 2007 to 2013.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","140866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896481","Home Office","false","2018-05-10","<p>The Government is satisfied that Public Spaces Protection Orders are an important tool in helping local authorities to tackle persistent and unreasonable anti-social behaviour that has a detrimental effect on others’ quality of life. In the refreshed statutory guidance on the use of the powers provided by the Anti-social Behaviour, Crime and Policing Act 2014, which was published on 24 December 2017, we stressed the importance of ensuring that all the relevant legal tests are met before making such an order. We also said that powers should be used appropriately to provide a proportionate response to the behaviour in question.</p><p>The Home Office is aware of Ealing Council’s decision to introduce a Public Spaces Protection Order outside the Marie Stopes abortion clinic in Ealing. This will be considered as part of the current Abortion Clinic Protest Review.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-05-10T14:15:50.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896481/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896481/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Public Spaces Protection Orders: Ealing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether the Government has made an assessment of the human rights implications of Ealing Council using a Public Spaces Protection Order to criminalise peaceful protest; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","140571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896482","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>The specific information requested is not included in statistics published by the Home Office. Published data on sponsorship applications can be found in the immigration statistics release.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/employer-sponsorship-restricted-certificate-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/employer-sponsorship-restricted-certificate-allocations</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-09T15:37:45.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896482/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896482/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Engineers and Scientists: Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 27 April to Question 137536, on Engineers and Scientists: Visas, whether the number of engineers and scientists who were refused a Tier 2 (General) Certificate of Sponsorship between May 2015 and November 2017 increased because the annual cap had been reached.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","140710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896483","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-09","<p>NHS Digital is working with all the devolved administrations to reconcile their respective record to trace the women affected. Once identified, Public Health England will send the appropriate letter to each of the identified women by the end of May 2018.</p><p> </p><p>No assessment has been made on the number of women who have moved to Wales and may not have been invited to their final breast screening. NHS Digital is working with all devolved administrations to reconcile the record to confirm a number.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","140672","2018-05-09T10:39:16.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896483/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896483/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896483/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how his Department intends to contact women who have moved to Wales who may not have been invited to their final breast screening due to computer failure as identified in the national breast screening programme in England; and what the timetable is for contacting those people.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","140671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896484","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-09","<p>NHS Digital is working with all the devolved administrations to reconcile their respective record to trace the women affected. Once identified, Public Health England will send the appropriate letter to each of the identified women by the end of May 2018.</p><p> </p><p>No assessment has been made on the number of women who have moved to Wales and may not have been invited to their final breast screening. NHS Digital is working with all devolved administrations to reconcile the record to confirm a number.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","140671","2018-05-09T10:39:16.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896484/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896484/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896484/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Breast Cancer: Screening","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate his Department has made of the number of women who have moved to Wales who may not have been invited to their final breast screening as a result of the computer failure in the national breast screening programme in England.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","140672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896485","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>As part of our on-going engagement with the steel industry, I can confirm that ministers and officials regularly engage with the steel producers, unions, trade associations, devolved administrations, the European Commission and our partners in the G20 Global Steel Forum, to discuss a range of issues concerning the steel industry.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-05-09T16:33:38.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896485/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896485/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896485/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-02","Steel Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, when he next plans to convene a Steel Council.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","140673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896486","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-10","<p>Each shale gas licensee (and there may be more than one for each licence) is responsible for their well(s).</p><p>The Government has been clear that it considers that the financial resilience of a company wishing to hydraulically fracture is a relevant consideration in the consents process. As set out in the Written Ministerial Statement of 25 January 2018, on Energy Policy, HCWS428, as a matter of policy we will look at the financial resilience of all companies wishing to carry out hydraulic fracturing operations alongside their application for Hydraulic Fracturing Consent to ensure companies have the financial capacity to meet their regulatory obligations, including protecting the environment.</p><p>If environmental damage does occur, remediation of the damage will be dealt with under the main regimes for dealing with contamination, the Environmental Damage (Prevention and Remediation) Regulations 2009 and Part IIA of the Environmental Protection Act 1990.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-10T14:37:11.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896486/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896486/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-02","Fracking: Environment Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he has taken to mitigate the costs to the public purse relating to recovery of environmental damage in the event that a company engaged in fracking becomes insolvent after fracking operations have begun.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","140538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896487","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-10","<p>I will be hosting the International Carbon Capture Utilisation and Storage (CCUS) conference which will take place on 28 and 29 November 2018 in Edinburgh. Its theme will be ‘Accelerating CCUS’.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the conference will be published on the Department’s website in June 2018.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-10T14:36:33.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896487/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896487/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896487/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-02","Carbon Capture and Storage: International Cooperation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 6 April 2018 to Question 133883, on what date he plans to publish the prospectus for the 2018 International Carbon Capture Utilisation and Storage event.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","140539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896488","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Government has set out that the UK is seeking the broadest and deepest possible future agreement with the EU, and that as part of that the UK will need to make a strong commitment that its regulatory standards will remain as high as the EU’s. We are making real progress in our negotiations, including agreeing the terms of an implementation period that will give Governments, businesses and citizens on both sides the time they need to prepare for our new relationship.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-05-14T16:48:25.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896488/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896488/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896488/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Construction: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 27 April 2018 to Question 136573 on Construction: Standards, what steps he is taking with his EU counterparts to ensure that the UK's design and civil engineering standards are maintained after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","140662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896489","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-10","<p>Maintaining affordable energy supplies for both the UK and the EU is a key objective of the Future Economic Partnership being sought by the UK.</p><p> </p><p>We want to continue arrangements that allow efficient trade of electricity to take place between the EU and the UK. However, the future trade agreement will be decided in negotiations, and we are unable to comment on these arrangements until negotiations conclude.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-10T14:35:44.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896489/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896489/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896489/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-02","Energy: UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect on the energy bills of (a) households and (b) businesses of the requirement for energy suppliers to pay EU transmission charges for access to the EU’s internal energy market after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","140540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896490","Wales Office","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Under-Secretary of State for Wales, Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth, discussed the matter with the Welsh Government Cabinet Secretary for Health and Social Services last week. Whilst the UK Government has offered support if required, any review of the process undertaken in Wales is a matter for the Welsh Government.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2018-05-14T09:55:33.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896490/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896490/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896490/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-05-02","Breast Cancer: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what discussions he has had with ministers in the Welsh Government on the NHS in Wales' breast-screening process being scrutinised by an independent reviewer.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","140605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896491","Wales Office","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Under-Secretary of State for Wales, Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth, discussed the matter with the Welsh Government Cabinet Secretary for Health and Social Services last week. The system used in Wales is a matter for the Welsh Government; however I understand that they use the same NBSS system as in England.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2018-05-14T09:56:44.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896491/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896491/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896491/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-05-02","Breast Cancer: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, whether the computing system used by the NHS in England which was responsible for the failure to register thousands of women for breast screening is the same system that is used in Wales.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","140606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896492","Wales Office","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Under-Secretary of State for Wales, Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth, discussed the matter with the Welsh Government Cabinet Secretary for Health and Social Services last week and offered support to Welsh Ministers. Separately, officials from Public Health England have been in discussions with Public Health Wales.</p><p> </p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns",,"2018-05-14T09:57:51.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896492/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896492/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896492/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-05-02","Breast Cancer: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what information he holds on when the Welsh Government became aware of the possibility that a faulty computing system in the NHS in Wales may have been responsible as in England for the failure to register thousands of women for breast screening.","false","Biography information for Ann Clwyd","Cynon Valley","Ann Clwyd","140607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896493","Department for Education","false","2018-06-11","<p>We are committed to supporting areas that are facing the greatest challenges, wherever they exist. As part of the 2016 Northern Powerhouse Schools Strategy, the government committed £70 million to support educational improvement in the north, up to the end of March 2020. Since that announcement, the government has spent or committed significantly more than £70 million to support educational improvement in the north. This spend includes a range of policies, some of which are additional for and only happening in the north, some of which are additional spend on existing policies in the north, and some of which represent the northern element of some key national funds. The attached table breaks this down by project and financial year.</p><p> </p><p>As well as the investment set out in the table, there will also be investment in the north through the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund (TLIF). TLIF providers have reported as at 30 April 2018 that approximately 130 schools and 2,250 teachers and leaders have been recruited across the north of England and will benefit from the bespoke continuing professional development programmes being delivered. Therefore as at 30 April 2018, DfE has allocated over £3.1 million of TLIF funding over the three financial years (2017-18, 2018-19, 2019-20) to support schools across the north of England. We expect further investment in the north through the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund during the financial years 2018-19 and 2019-20.</p><p>The following providers, funded via the first procurement round of the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund, cover schools in the north:</p><ul><li>Ruth Miskin Training</li><li>Teacher Development Trust</li><li>Edison Learning</li><li>STEM Learning</li><li>Teach First</li><li>Institute of Physics</li><li>Institute for Teaching</li></ul>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","140738 ; 140739","2018-06-11T16:18:54.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896493/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896493/answer","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improvement_in_the_North.pdf","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improvement_in_the_North.pdf","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improve","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improve","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896493/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896493/answer/previousversion/56737","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2018-05-02","Education: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much funding has been allocated from the public purse to the Northern Powerhouse Education Fund in each year since it was established; and what estimate he has made of the level of funding from the public purse to that Fund in each of the next three financial years.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","140737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896494","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-21","<p>My Department continues to work on plans to ensure a smooth and orderly Brexit. We engage stakeholders from relevant sectors, including local government and communities, on a regular basis as part of the Department’s usual business and to understand the opportunities and implications of Brexit.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-05-21T15:35:38.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896494/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896494/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896494/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 27 April 2018 to Question 136658 on Local Government Finance, answered 27 April 2018, whether his Department has plans to produce impact assessments based on the different EU exit scenarios.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","140663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896495","Department for Education","false","2018-06-11","<p>We are committed to supporting areas that are facing the greatest challenges, wherever they exist. As part of the 2016 Northern Powerhouse Schools Strategy, the government committed £70 million to support educational improvement in the north, up to the end of March 2020. Since that announcement, the government has spent or committed significantly more than £70 million to support educational improvement in the north. This spend includes a range of policies, some of which are additional for and only happening in the north, some of which are additional spend on existing policies in the north, and some of which represent the northern element of some key national funds. The attached table breaks this down by project and financial year.</p><p> </p><p>As well as the investment set out in the table, there will also be investment in the north through the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund (TLIF). TLIF providers have reported as at 30 April 2018 that approximately 130 schools and 2,250 teachers and leaders have been recruited across the north of England and will benefit from the bespoke continuing professional development programmes being delivered. Therefore as at 30 April 2018, DfE has allocated over £3.1 million of TLIF funding over the three financial years (2017-18, 2018-19, 2019-20) to support schools across the north of England. We expect further investment in the north through the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund during the financial years 2018-19 and 2019-20.</p><p>The following providers, funded via the first procurement round of the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund, cover schools in the north:</p><ul><li>Ruth Miskin Training</li><li>Teacher Development Trust</li><li>Edison Learning</li><li>STEM Learning</li><li>Teach First</li><li>Institute of Physics</li><li>Institute for Teaching</li></ul>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","140737 ; 140739","2018-06-11T16:18:54.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896495/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896495/answer","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improvement_in_the_North.pdf","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improvement_in_the_North.pdf","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improve","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improve","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896495/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896495/answer/previousversion/56889","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2018-05-02","Education: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much and what proportion of funding for the Northern Powerhouse Education Fund has been spent in each year since the fund was established.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","140738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896496","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-17","<p>Officials across my Department routinely engage with policy teams across Whitehall and with local government officials on the impacts of Brexit. Discussions take place in a range of fora and information on the timings of these meetings is not held centrally.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-05-17T15:22:31.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896496/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896496/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896496/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 27 April 2018 to Question 136658 on Local Government Finance, if he will publish the dates of the meetings that officials in his Department held with (a) policy teams from across Whitehall and (b) local government officials on the impact of the UK's exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","140664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896497","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-10","<p>A decision on the appointment of the national Tree Champion, including to whom that person will report, will be made in due course.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-10T14:19:22.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896497/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896497/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896497/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-02","Forestry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when he plans to appoint the national tree champion; and to whom that person will report.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","140695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896498","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-14","<p>HM Treasury’s Consolidated Budgeting Guidance applies to all departments. The budgeting system tries to ensure that departments have good incentives to manage their business well, to prioritise across programmes, and to obtain value for money. There are rules allowing departments to offset certain income against budgets. Only some of the income that comes to a department benefits budgets and this is forecast at the start of each Spending Review. The main categories of MHCLG income are income from rent of buildings, sales of services and fees and interest on loans.</p><p>MHCLG agreed additional flexibility to retain income that was above our forecast at the start of the Spending Review at Autumn Budget.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-05-14T16:26:17.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896498/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896498/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896498/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 26 April 2018 to Question 136575 on Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Brexit,  what definition his Department uses for additional flexibility in relation to retaining income at future Budgets.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","140665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896499","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Department holds Train Operating Companies to account through its contractual mechanisms, and meets regularly with operators to review performance levels and plans for improvements. It also works closely with ORR, in its role as regulator, in overseeing Network Rail’s performance levels. The department has also increased its engagement across industry to promote industry sharing of good practice and a top down focus on the day to day performance of the railway. In addition we require all bidders for new rail franchises to describe how they will work in an integrated manner with Network Rail to achieve better performance for passengers.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-05-09T13:08:42.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896499/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896499/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896499/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Railways: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to review his Department’s policy on the performance management of rail franchises.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","140750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896500","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Department continuously assesses the performance of its forecasts and seeks to improve them by commissioning research, as well as reviewing work completed elsewhere, to ensure that we are using the latest available evidence. The Department assesses the performance of its forecasts by carrying out “backcasting” exercises, whereby our forecasting technique is applied historically to see how the forecasts compare to actual passenger numbers. Some backcasts were published in the Rail Demand Forecasting Estimation study phase 2 report (<a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/610059/phase2-rail-demand-forecasting-estimation-study.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/610059/phase2-rail-demand-forecasting-estimation-study.pdf</a> ). Further, the Department carries out peer reviews on new forecasting evidence, and compares its techniques to those used by other rail forecasting bodies, as well as learning from other industries.</p><p> </p><p>The Department endeavours to improve its rail forecasting by commissioning research and collaborating with industry partners and others in the Passenger Demand Forecasting Council (PDFC). PDFC have recently revised their evidence base in a new version of the Passenger Demand Forecasting Handbook.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-05-09T13:12:42.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896500/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896500/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896500/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Railways: Passengers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to (a) assess the effectiveness of and (b) improve the Department’s processes for rail passenger demand forecasting.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","140751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896501","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-10","<p>Maintaining affordable energy supplies for both the UK and the EU is a key objective of the future partnership we are seeking. A well-functioning energy market is of vital importance for the European economy and we share the ambition to make energy trading easier by opening up new markets and increasing the level of interconnection between them.</p><p> </p><p>Leaving the EU will not change any of our domestic statutory commitments to reduce our emissions, as laid out in the Climate Change Act 2008. The UK remains committed to the Paris Climate Change Agreement and, whatever our future partnership with the EU, we will satisfy our international obligations under the Agreement.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-10T14:35:59.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896501/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896501/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896501/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-02","Climate Change and Electricity Interconnectors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the UK leaving the EU on (a) levels of interconnection for power trading between the UK and the EU and (b) the UK meeting its targets on climate change.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","140541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896502","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-09","<p>Performance has improved for Govia Thameslink Railway passengers following the height of industrial action. The Department decided enforcement measures through a remedial plan was the appropriate course of action.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-05-09T12:58:46.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896502/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896502/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896502/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Thameslink, Southern and Great Northern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons he decided not to cancel Govia Thameslink’s contract to operate the TSGN route in early 2017.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","140752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896503","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-10","<p>The Government’s priority is to maintain secure, affordable and clean energy supplies for businesses and households. We share the EU’s ambition to increase the level of interconnection across the region where it delivers these benefits and is in consumer’s interests.</p><p> </p><p>The UK continues to see investment in new interconnection projects. In addition to the 4GW currently operational, 4.4GW of new interconnector capacity is already under construction. Positive investment decisions on two new projects, making up 2GW of this capacity, have taken place since the referendum.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-10T14:36:15.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896503/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896503/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896503/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-02","Electricity Interconnectors: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment the Government has made of the effect of the UK leaving the EU on the merits of investing in new electricity interconnectors between the UK and EU member states.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","140542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896504","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>In immigration routes which awarded points for an applicant’s UK earnings, we must be satisfied that those earnings are genuine.</p><p>Where we identify discrepancies between the income declared to the Home Office and to HMRC, we give applicants an opportunity to explain the reasons for the discrepancies. We will take into consideration the nature of the discrepancy, all available evidence and any explanation from the applicant before making a decision.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-09T15:52:58.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896504/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896504/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896504/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the criteria are for the use of a case arising from the tax affairs of an individual that was settled by HMRC in a decision to refuse an application by that person for renewed leave to remain in the UK; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","140547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896505","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>Early diagnosis of blood cancers is difficult as symptoms, such as tiredness or back pain, are often misdiagnosed. For suspected blood cancers, the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence published a revised guideline in 2015 which clearly sets out that general practitioners should consider a very urgent full blood count within 48 hours to assess for leukaemia if adults present with suspicious symptoms.</p><p> </p><p>In December 2016 NHS England announced transformation funding of £200 million for Cancer Alliances to encourage new and innovative ways to diagnose cancer earlier, improve the care for those living with cancer and ensure that each cancer patient gets the right care for them.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, the Accelerate, Coordinate and Evaluate Programme is a unique early diagnosis initiative, a programme of 60 projects exploring innovative concepts of diagnosing cancer earlier across England. The programme is testing a new multi-disciplinary diagnostic centre approach to diagnosing patients with vague or unclear but concerning symptoms, often characteristic of hard to diagnose cancers like blood cancers.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-14T11:23:24.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896505/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896505/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896505/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Haematological Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans his Department has to ensure people with blood cancer are diagnosed as soon as possible.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","140696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896506","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Recovery Package is designed to help patients and clinicians assess a patient’s holistic needs and plan appropriately for their care and support. It includes a Holistic Needs Assessment (HNA) and Care Plan. This guides a conversation about the person’s holistic needs (physical, psychosocial, financial and social) in order to identify any concerns. An HNA should take place within 31 days of diagnosis and at the end of each acute phase of treatment and the Care Plan updated each time. The Recovery Package is being commissioned and delivered in full or in part by many clinical commissioning groups and providers across England. Our aim now is to accelerate the process, to ensure full implementation by 2020 - available to all cancer patients.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","140698 ; 140700","2018-05-14T11:25:00.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896506/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896506/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896506/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Haematological Cancer: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he is taking to ensure that (a) emotional and (b) psychological support is provided to people who have blood cancer.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","140697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896507","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>Parliament legislated to amend the appeals system in the Immigration Act 2014 so that an appeal only arises where a claim raising asylum, humanitarian protection or human rights is refused. Similar provisions are set out in the Immigration (European Economic Area) Regulations 2016. The Government has no plans to change the appeals system.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-09T15:12:27.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896507/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896507/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896507/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Immigrants: English Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will make it his policy that an applicant whose leave to remain has been cancelled because of an allegation of cheating in a Toeic English language test will be able to submit an appeal in the UK.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","140548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896508","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Recovery Package is designed to help patients and clinicians assess a patient’s holistic needs and plan appropriately for their care and support. It includes a Holistic Needs Assessment (HNA) and Care Plan. This guides a conversation about the person’s holistic needs (physical, psychosocial, financial and social) in order to identify any concerns. An HNA should take place within 31 days of diagnosis and at the end of each acute phase of treatment and the Care Plan updated each time. The Recovery Package is being commissioned and delivered in full or in part by many clinical commissioning groups and providers across England. Our aim now is to accelerate the process, to ensure full implementation by 2020 - available to all cancer patients.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","140697 ; 140700","2018-05-14T11:25:00.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896508/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896508/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896508/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Haematological Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he is taking to ensure that the cancer recovery package meets the needs of people with blood cancer.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","140698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896509","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>Public Health England and NHS England developed the first iteration of the cancer dashboard in response to recommendations in the Independent Cancer Taskforce report ‘Achieving world-class cancer outcomes: a strategy for England 2015-2020’. This includes data on breast, colorectal, lung and prostate cancers. Further cancer sites, including blood cancer, were not included because of the risk of making patients identifiable when viewing data for individual hospitals or clinical commissioning groups.</p><p> </p><p>A second iteration of the dashboard is being considered by the National Cancer Transformation Board with a wider ambition to include rarer cancers and cancers with a lower incidence, such a blood cancers, as the dashboard develops.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-14T11:28:20.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896509/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896509/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896509/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Haematological Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what plans his Department has to widen the cancer dashboard to include blood cancer.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","140699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896510","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>There is an urgent need to entrust the facts of what happened during the recent protests in Gaza. The UK is supportive of an investigation which establishes the facts about the recent violence in Gaza. Given the importance of accountability, we urge that any investigation is independent and transparent, its findings are made public, and if wrongdoing is found, that those responsible be held to account.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-09T16:02:24.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896510/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896510/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896510/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 19 April 2018 to Question 135976, by what criteria he has assessed that Israel's investigation into the killings of protesters in Gaza will be independent and transparent.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","140561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896511","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Recovery Package is designed to help patients and clinicians assess a patient’s holistic needs and plan appropriately for their care and support. It includes a Holistic Needs Assessment (HNA) and Care Plan. This guides a conversation about the person’s holistic needs (physical, psychosocial, financial and social) in order to identify any concerns. An HNA should take place within 31 days of diagnosis and at the end of each acute phase of treatment and the Care Plan updated each time. The Recovery Package is being commissioned and delivered in full or in part by many clinical commissioning groups and providers across England. Our aim now is to accelerate the process, to ensure full implementation by 2020 - available to all cancer patients.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","140697 ; 140698","2018-05-14T11:25:00.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896511/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896511/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896511/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Haematological Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what support his Department provides to people diagnosed with blood cancer.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","140700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896512","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-10","<p>The capital grant scheme for peat restoration received 5 applications for funds.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-10T14:28:09.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896512/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896512/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896512/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-02","Peat Bogs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many applications for funds he has had for the capital grant scheme for peat restoration.","false","Biography information for Dr Alan Whitehead","Southampton, Test","Dr Alan Whitehead","140543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896513","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>In England there is a well-established framework for enabling access to cost effective new cancer medicines. All new licensed cancer medicines are referred to the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) for inclusion within the Technology Appraisal Programme. This referral is irrespective of the clinical indication concerned. Where cancer medicines are approved by NICE for use in England, NHS England makes these available immediately. NICE now also has the ability to refer licensed medicines demonstrating promising, but not yet certain, benefits for inclusion within the Cancer Drugs Fund.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-14T15:37:08.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896513/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896513/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896513/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Haematological Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of funding for providing new treatments for blood cancer.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","140701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896514","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>Tests within the UK were provided by ETS Global BV. They had their licence suspended in early February 2014. This license expired on 5 April 2014 and they were removed from the immigration rules on 1 July 2014. Information on current providers is available at the following link: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/guidance-on-applying-for-uk-visa-approved-english-language-tests" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/guidance-on-applying-for-uk-visa-approved-english-language-tests</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-09T15:10:43.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896514/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896514/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896514/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Educational Testing Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what sanctions his Department imposed on the American firm ETS after Panorama revealed in 2014 that there had been cheating in some of that company's Test of English for International Communication tests.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","140549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896515","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>Saudi Arabia has publicly stated that it is committed to investigating incidents of potential concern arising from the air campaign in Yemen and that any lessons will be acted upon. The Saudi-led Coalition set up a Joint Incidents Assessment Team (JIAT) in May 2016 to investigate and report on such incidents. The JIAT continues to release the outcomes of its investigations. We welcome this. To date, the JIAT has announced the findings of a total of 55 investigations, with the most recent being released on 5 March 2018. Although the UK does not have a role in JIAT investigations, we have provided advice and support to the JIAT to help it strengthen its processes. Assessing compliance with international humanitarian law, is part of the UK’s arms export licensing process, which is one of the most robust in the world. We review all relevant factors including the effectiveness of measures to identify and learn lessons from incidents of potential concern.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-09T16:04:24.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896515/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896515/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896515/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to make an assessment of the effectiveness of Saudi Arabia's investigation into airstrikes carried out in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","140562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896516","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>As previously set out to the Home Affairs Select committee in writing, a number of steps were taken to ensure that the ETS process for declaring test results invalid was suitably robust. This included commissioning an independent expert report from a leading Professor of Forensic Speech Science which concluded that the number of false matches would be very small, and that the system used were more likely to produce false negatives than false positives. The Courts have found that the core evidence we have is sufficient to establish a presumption of fraud.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-09T15:48:58.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896516/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896516/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896516/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Educational Testing Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment his Department has made of the credibility of the allegations made by ETS that people cheated in the Test of English for International Communication.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","140550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896517","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>Our understanding of the methods used by ETS to identify invalid tests has been set out in writing to the Home Affairs Select Committee. These responses are publicly available. The Courts have consistently found the core evidence we have is sufficient to establish a presumption of fraud. It is then up to individuals to challenge this through statutory appeals where applicable or Judicial Review.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-09T15:15:29.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896517/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896517/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896517/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-05-02","Educational Testing Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what methods ETS has used to identify cheating in Test of English for International Communication tests; and what opportunities are available to people who want to challenge (a) allegations and (b) findings of cheating in those tests.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","140551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896518","Department for Education","false","2018-06-11","<p>We are committed to supporting areas that are facing the greatest challenges, wherever they exist. As part of the 2016 Northern Powerhouse Schools Strategy, the government committed £70 million to support educational improvement in the north, up to the end of March 2020. Since that announcement, the government has spent or committed significantly more than £70 million to support educational improvement in the north. This spend includes a range of policies, some of which are additional for and only happening in the north, some of which are additional spend on existing policies in the north, and some of which represent the northern element of some key national funds. The attached table breaks this down by project and financial year.</p><p> </p><p>As well as the investment set out in the table, there will also be investment in the north through the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund (TLIF). TLIF providers have reported as at 30 April 2018 that approximately 130 schools and 2,250 teachers and leaders have been recruited across the north of England and will benefit from the bespoke continuing professional development programmes being delivered. Therefore as at 30 April 2018, DfE has allocated over £3.1 million of TLIF funding over the three financial years (2017-18, 2018-19, 2019-20) to support schools across the north of England. We expect further investment in the north through the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund during the financial years 2018-19 and 2019-20.</p><p>The following providers, funded via the first procurement round of the Teaching and Leadership Innovation Fund, cover schools in the north:</p><ul><li>Ruth Miskin Training</li><li>Teacher Development Trust</li><li>Edison Learning</li><li>STEM Learning</li><li>Teach First</li><li>Institute of Physics</li><li>Institute for Teaching</li></ul>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","140737 ; 140738","2018-06-11T16:18:54.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896518/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896518/answer","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improvement_in_the_North.pdf","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improvement_in_the_North.pdf","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improve","140737_140738_140739_Supporting_Education_Improve","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896518/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896518/answer/previousversion/57832","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2018-05-02","Education: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much funding each (a) project, (b) organisation and (c) initiative received from the Northern Powerhouse Education Fund; and in what year that funding was allocated.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","140739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896519","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-11","<p>My Department is working with Network Rail to progress the design and development of the Western Rail Link to Heathrow scheme and a final consultation on the proposed alignment will commence this month.</p><p> </p><p>This is a major step in the development of the scheme and is required before Network Rail can submit its application to the Planning Inspectorate for the necessary consents. The construction timetable is subject to obtaining these planning consents but an indicative timetable would see this commence during Network Rail’s Control Period 6 (the funding period 2019 to 2024).</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-05-11T10:25:52.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896519/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896519/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896519/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Heathrow Airport: Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timetable is for work to (a) commence and (b) finish on the Western Rail Access to Heathrow project.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","140868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896520","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-09","<p>A new Western Rail Link to Heathrow would substantially reduce rail journey times to Heathrow for passengers from the Thames Valley, South Coast, South West, South Wales and West Midlands, eliminating the need to change at London Paddington and encouraging modal shift.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to benefits for airport passengers and workers, the proposed link would provide a real boost to the economy, generating economic growth and new jobs across the Thames Valley and surrounding areas.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-05-09T14:41:55.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896520/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896520/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Heathrow Airport: Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential economic benefit to the South West of the proposed Western Rail Access to Heathrow.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","140869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896521","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>The UK’s Policy is to support a two-state solution: a secure Israel living side by side a viable and contiguous Palestinian state which is why we voted for UN Security Council Resolution 2334. The UK’s dealings with the state of Israel and the Occupied Palestinian Territories reflect this policy.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-09T16:05:21.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896521/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896521/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Israeli Settlements: UN Resolutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to UN Security Council Resolution 2334 adopted in December 2016, what steps his Department has taken to distinguish in the UK's relevant dealings between the territory of the State of Israel and the territories occupied since 1967.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","140563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896522","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>UN Security Council Resolution 2334 asks the Secretary-General to report to the Council every three months on the implementation of its provisions. We will continue to monitor the situation closely. On 26 March Nikolay Mladenov , the UN Special Coordinator for the Middle East Peace Process, delivered his most recent report on the implementation of Security Council Resolution 2334.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-09T16:06:57.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896522/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896522/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Israeli Settlements: UN Resolutions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to ensure the full adherence to and implementation of UN Security Council Resolution 2334.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","140564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896523","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>My ministerial team and I observe the correct parliamentary protocols on notifying the sitting MP when making a visit to a Northern Ireland constituency.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2018-05-09T12:26:46.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896523/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896523/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-05-02","Domestic Visits: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether she observes parliamentary protocols on notifying the sitting MP when making a visit to a Northern Ireland constituency; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","140645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896524","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>We will ensure the UK benefits from world-changing economic trends to build the industries of the future. In our Industrial Strategy we have set out four Grand Challenges where Britain can lead the global technological revolution: in artificial intelligence and the data revolution; the global shift to clean growth; the ageing society; and the future of mobility – where we will build on our strengths to shape new markets and enhance the UK’s competitive advantage.</p><p> </p><p>As we made clear in the Industrial Strategy White Paper, we will use all the policy levers at our disposal, including government procurement, to achieve success in the Grand Challenges. We will drive innovation not only by supporting research and development, but also through the creation and shaping of new markets. Where appropriate, we will look to take a mission-oriented approach to guide these efforts, bringing industry, researchers and government together to solve practical problems and accelerate innovation.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-05-09T11:50:56.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896524/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896524/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-05-02","Industry: Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the report, Mission-Oriented Research & Innovation: A problem-solving approach to fuel innovation-led growth, published by the European Commission on 22 February 2018, whether he plans to adopt a mission-based procurement approach as recommended in that report as part of the Government's Industrial Strategy.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","140716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896525","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-14","<p>Departmental officials have been in regular contact with the supplier of Epipens, Mylan, and are working closely with them to resolve the supply situation as quickly as possible. Supplies are currently available, although limited, and are being closely managed to ensure that pharmacies can obtain stock to fulfil prescriptions for patients.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-14T15:34:00.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896525/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896525/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-05-02","Allergies: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has (a) made to and (b) received from manufacturers representations on supply problems affecting the availability of EpiPens.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","140565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896526","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Local Government Transparency Code 2015 already sets out what procurement and spend information local authorities should publish and the format in which it should be published to ensure transparency and comparability across authorities.</p><p>I am aware some councils publish on open data hubs to enable comparability and I welcome this.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-05-09T16:49:59.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896526/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896526/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-05-02","Local Government: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will take steps to improve the transparency and comparability of local authority records on procurement spending with small businesses.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","140717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896527","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-15","<p>From 2 October to 20 November 2017, an independent working group set up under the Litter Strategy for England held a call for evidence on measures to reduce littering of drinks containers and promote recycling. This included metal drinks containers that are sold sealed and used for the sale of alcoholic or non-alcoholic beverages, often for consumption ‘on the go’. It involved seeking evidence on the costs, benefits and impacts of deposit and reward and return schemes. Early this year, Ministers received and reviewed the working group’s report summarising its call for evidence and recommendations. This can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/drinks-containers-reducing-litter-and-increasing-recycling-call-for-evidence" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/consultations/drinks-containers-reducing-litter-and-increasing-recycling-call-for-evidence</a>.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has confirmed that it will introduce a deposit return scheme in England, subject to a consultation later this year. The consultation will look at the details of how such a scheme would work, alongside other measures to increase recycling rates.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-15T15:12:18.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896527/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896527/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-02","Beverage Containers: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of implementing a deposit return scheme for aluminium cans.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","140566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896528","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-16","<p>The Minister responsible for this policy area, Minister Coffey, visited Norway, Sweden and Denmark late last year to find out more about the deposit return schemes (DRS) in those countries, including meeting the then Danish Minister for Environment and Food to discuss the Danish DRS.</p><p> </p><p>The Secretary of State has not had any specific discussions on DRS with his counterparts in Denmark, Sweden or Germany</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-16T10:11:19.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896528/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896528/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-02","Beverage Containers: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions he has had with his counterparts in (a) Denmark, (b) Sweden and (c) Germany on deposit return schemes for single use drinks containers.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","140567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896529","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-10","<p>There are no Departmental targets relating to the number of sanctions made against claimants of Universal Credit.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-05-10T15:48:54.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896529/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896529/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896529/answer/previousversion/56788","Biography information for Alok Sharma","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-05-02","Universal Credit: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether there are any targets relating to the number of sanctions made against claimants of universal credit.","false","Biography information for Danielle Rowley","Midlothian","Danielle Rowley","140851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896530","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Office of Rail and Road (ORR) has made significant changes to its regulatory approach to inform the planning for CP6, with an increased emphasis on route-level regulation of Network Rail and bottom-up appraisals of the deliverability and efficiency of its plans. These changes will increase transparency, creating stronger incentives on Network Rail to ensure improvements to its unit costs, efficiency and productivity, as well as to further improve the ORR’s ability to monitor Network Rail and hold it to account. The Government is working closely with the ORR to support these changes and improve the efficiency of the railway, whilst being mindful of the ORR’s statutory independence from Government and its accountability to Parliament for the effective delivery of its functions.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","140754","2018-05-09T13:03:07.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896530/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896530/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Network Rail: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of Office for Rail and Road’s plans to monitor Network Rail’s (a) unit costs and (b) productivity at route level in Control Period 6.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","140753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896531","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>As the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland told the House on 21 March 2018, any representations made to her by political parties regarding the salaries and allowances for Members of the Northern Ireland Assembly will be published, subject to any necessary redaction of sensitive or personal data. Any such representations will be published by the Northern Ireland Office.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-05-09T12:27:59.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896531/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896531/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-05-02","Northern Ireland Assembly: Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if she will place in the Library copies of the representations she has received from political parties in Northern Ireland on the subject of reducing the salaries of Members of the Legislative Assembly; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","140646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896532","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Office of Rail and Road (ORR) has made significant changes to its regulatory approach to inform the planning for CP6, with an increased emphasis on route-level regulation of Network Rail and bottom-up appraisals of the deliverability and efficiency of its plans. These changes will increase transparency, creating stronger incentives on Network Rail to ensure improvements to its unit costs, efficiency and productivity, as well as to further improve the ORR’s ability to monitor Network Rail and hold it to account. The Government is working closely with the ORR to support these changes and improve the efficiency of the railway, whilst being mindful of the ORR’s statutory independence from Government and its accountability to Parliament for the effective delivery of its functions.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","140753","2018-05-09T13:03:07.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896532/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896532/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-05-02","Network Rail: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the (a) incentives and (b) disincentives the Office for Rail and Road proposes to bring forward in CP6 to ensure improvements to Network Rail’s (i) unit costs and (ii) productivity in Control Period 6.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","140754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896533","Women and Equalities","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Government signed the Istanbul Convention to signal the UK’s strong commitment to tackling violence against women and girls (VAWG). As the November 2017 progress report sets out, in most respects the UK already complies with, or goes further than the Convention requires. We have significantly strengthened the legislative framework; introduced new protective tools; and issued a range of guidance and support for frontline professionals.</p><p> </p><p>We have always been clear on our commitment to ratifying the Convention. The Domestic Abuse Bill will be another step towards meeting that commitment by extending extraterritorial jurisdiction over offences required by the Convention which, for England and Wales, is the final legislative step necessary for ratification. We are consulting widely as we develop the proposals for the draft Domestic Abuse Bill, and launched a public consultation on 8 March, International Women’s Day. We are keen to hear from experts, including charities, service providers and legal experts, to understand their views and ensure that the voices of domestic abuse victims and survivors are heard.</p><p> </p><p>As the criminal law and the majority of the areas covered by the Convention are devolved to Scotland and Northern Ireland, the Devolved Administrations are considering what legislative or other changes are necessary for compliance with the Convention in their territories. The Government liaises regularly with the Devolved Administrations on VAWG issues and we will continue working closely with the Scottish Government and Northern Ireland Executive to ensure we are taking a coordinated approach on this agenda.</p><p> </p><p>We are also in ongoing discussions with the voluntary and community sector on these issues, and in line with the requirement of section 2 of the Preventing and Combating Violence Against Women and Domestic Violence (Ratification of Convention) Act 2017, we will set out a timetable for ratification in due course.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-05-14T16:58:26.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896533/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896533/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-05-02","Council of Europe Convention On Preventing and Combating Violence Against Women and Domestic Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what the timetable is for the ratification of the Istanbul Convention.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","140745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896534","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>UK funding to support the Khartoum Process goes via the EU's Emergency Trust Fund (EUTF). The EUTF's current funding window (2015 - 2020) for the Horn of Africa, including the Khartoum Process, is 1.2bn euros, of which the UK contributes approximately 15%.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-05-09T14:10:31.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896534/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896534/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-05-02","Horn of Africa: Migration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much funding the Government is providing to the Khartoum process.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","140555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896535","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-09","<p>The United Kingdom National Screening Committee has produced reviews on the effectiveness of screening for the following cancers; the breast, bowel, cervical screening programmes are effective. Prostate, lung, ovary, mouth, gastric, and bladder are not recommended as there is not enough evidence to suggest that they are effective. Further information is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://legacyscreening.phe.org.uk/screening-recommendations.php" target="_blank">https://legacyscreening.phe.org.uk/screening-recommendations.php</a></p><p> </p><p>Public Health England will contact all the women affected living within the UK who are registered with a general practitioner before the end of May with the first 65,000 letters going out this week.</p><p> </p><p>The breast screening programme was started in 1988 and rolled out over three years. It originally invited women aged 50 to 64. Following pilots in the late 1990s screening was extended for women aged up to 70 between 2001 and 2006 in line with the National Health Service Cancer Plan. The Cancer Reform Strategy (2007) outlined plan to extend the age range of breast screening to offer screening to all women aged 47-73 years in England from 2012. However, to gather as much evidence as possible on screening the extended age ranges, the decision was taken for the extension to become a randomised controlled trial (AgeX). Further information is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/+/http://www.dh.gov.uk/en/Publicationsandstatistics/Publications/PublicationsPolicyAndGuidance/Browsable/DH_4990751" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/+/http://www.dh.gov.uk/en/Publicationsandstatistics/Publications/PublicationsPolicyAndGuidance/Browsable/DH_4990751</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","140735 ; 140736","2018-05-09T