"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896552","Department for Education","false","2018-05-09","<p>The government funds local authorities to deliver the free entitlements in line with our regulations and guidance. It is the responsibility of local authorities to collect information from providers for funding purposes.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-05-09T15:40:42.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896552/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/896552/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-02","Day Care and Pre-school Education: Religion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what information his Department holds on the spending of funds from the public purse on childcare and early years education provided by religious organisations.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","140837"
