"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897076","Department for Education","false","2018-05-16","<p>The government has commissioned an independent evaluation of the first year of delivery, which will be published in summer 2018. As with the evaluations of early implementation and early rollout, we will use the evidence from this report to inform future delivery.</p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton",,"2018-05-16T15:14:13.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897076/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897076/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-02","Children: Day Care","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the costs and benefits of extending the 30 hours free childcare for three and four year olds to families where parents are in training to prepare for work.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Durham",,"The Lord Bishop of Durham","HL7500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897077","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-16","<p>We expect the final Circular Economy Package to be adopted shortly. The Government has confirmed that the UK will vote in favour of the final package. The Government is currently developing its approach to transposition and will set this out in the Resource and Waste Strategy later this year.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2018-05-16T10:48:59.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897077/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897077/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-05-02","Recycling: EU Law","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they have taken to ensure that the UK will transpose the European Commission Circular Economy Package into UK law within the timeframe to which they have committed.","false","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone",,"Baroness Featherstone","HL7501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897078","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-15","<p>The Department for International Development works closely with partner governments, donors, multilateral bodies and non-governmental organisations to ensure children are in school and learning.</p><p>We support education bilaterally in 20 countries: Afghanistan, Bangladesh, Burma, DRC, Ethiopia, Ghana, Jordan, Lebanon, Malawi, Nigeria, Occupied Palestinian Territories, Pakistan, Rwanda, Sierra Leone, South Sudan, Syria, Tanzania, Uganda, Zambia, and Zimbabwe.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2018-05-15T16:43:19.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897078/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897078/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-02","Developing Countries: Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government with which countries they engage in bilateral education programmes.","false","Biography information for Lord German",,"Lord German","HL7502"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897079","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-14","<p>The full list of countries deemed eligible for reciprocal visits has not yet been finalised and will be published in due course.</p><p>The criteria applied in this decision include whether the country is a priority for DFID and the British Council, and whether an appropriate degree of support for reciprocal visits can be offered in-country. However, exceptions are considered for countries which have strong links with regions of the UK.</p>",,"Lord Bates","HL7504 ; HL7505","2018-05-14T14:26:19.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897079/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/897079/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-05-02","Developing Countries: Educational Exchanges","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government which countries they have determined as being eligible for the reciprocal visits element of the Connecting Classrooms programme.","false","Biography information for Lord German",,"Lord German","HL7503"
