"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/895321","Department for Education","false","2018-05-08","<p>The requirement that students in receipt of Disabled Students’ Allowance make a £200 contribution towards the costs of computer hardware was introduced in 2015. The government has no current plans to review the size of that contribution.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-05-08T12:11:41.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/895321/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/895321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/895321/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-05-01","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether his Department plans to change its policy on the threshold for self-contribution of disabled students in receipt of Disabled Students' Allowance; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","139972"
